  <description><![CDATA[<p>Chalet Dahlia is an attractive chalet apartment on the edge of the piste, sleeping up to twelve people - it is ideal for a group of family and friends travelling to<span> </span><a data-udi="umb://document/4c93b881bd494483871697b278b37899" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4c93b881bd494483871697b278b37899}" title="La Rosière">La Rosiere</a>. The chalet has its own host, who will look after you throughout the week, you can enjoy six days of chalet catering including a skiers breakfast, afternoon tea and delicious evening meals with wine included. Chalet Dahlia is shared with our sister company Esprit Ski who specialise in family ski holidays and childcare.<span></span></p>
<h2>Perfect location</h2>
<p>If you like hitting the slopes as early as possible and getting back in time for the après ski, you'll benefit choosing this catered ski chalet. Located 150 metres from the ski lifts, the chalet is a great choice for the keen skiers and boarders - plus the centre of resort is only a short walk away so you can make the most of the bars La Rosiere has to offer.</p>
<h2>Family friendly</h2>
<p><span>Chalet Dahlia is perfect for families, it is shared with our sister company Esprit Ski who specialise in family skiing holidays and childcare. La Rosiere is one of Esprit's main hubs for childcare, which can include infant care, Snow Club, Xtra lessons and Mountain Academy. Children booked into Esprit children’s ski lessons will be collected by our Esprit Rangers from the chalet and taken to the ski school meeting place. When booking this chalet with Inghams you can book your children into our Esprit childcare, just give our Reservations team a call to book.</span></p>
<h2>Ideal for sole occupancy groups </h2>
<p>With attractive bedrooms and the possibility to accommodate up to 12 people, invite your family and your friends to spend a week in this cosy chalet. The warm and welcoming lounge is a great spot to catch up with your family and friends with a bit of cake and a coffee after a day on the slopes. There is also a shared sauna downstairs for guests staying in the Ferme D'Elisa chalets.</p>
<h3><span>Our chalets are going greener, so our mountains don't</span></h3>
<p>Our menu is changing for the better. In all of our chalets we're giving you more choice, with both meat-free and meat options on offer throughout your stay. This is driven as part of our commitment to reduce our <a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://document/67e40dbb55ff45098496ea2e7eee1f72" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/about-us/sustainability" target="_blank" title="Sustainability">carbon footprint</a>.</p>]]></description>
